</article>


<article>
  <h3 class="mt-5">Customize Links and URL's</h3>
  <p class="w-75">Open and edit <code>config/routes.rb</code></p>

<pre class="bg-light px-3"><code><span class="badge badge-secondary float-right mt-2">CODE EDITOR</span>
Rails.application.routes.draw <span class="block">do</span>

  <span class="comment"># Set Root Path</span>
  <span class="method">root</span> 'pages#home'

  <span class="comment"># Set Custom URL for Pages </span>
  <span class="method">get</span> 'product' => 'pages#product'
  <span class="method">get</span> 'long/useless/deep/link/pricing' => 'pages#pricing'

<span class="block">end</span>

</code></pre>
<p>By default, the product page URL will be <code>http://localhost:3000/pages/product</code>,
  matching the Controller and Action name.</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>http://localhost:3000/product</code> will now show <code>app/views/pages/product.html.erb</code></li>
  <li><code>http://localhost:3000/long/useless/deep/link/pricing</code> will now show <code>app/views/pages/pricing.html.erb</code></li>
</ul>
</article>
